              <div class="quotetitle">dak wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Frennzy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">&quot;Tube&quot; benders are for the more rigid piping...soft copper coils can easily be bent by hand.</div><br />Not the lever type ones to get the proper angle, I'm talking about the spring type ones that prevent kinking.</div><br /><br />Again, you don't need one.  A firm grip and a thumb are all that are necessary.  Just don't grab the coil far apart and go all HULK SMASH on it, and you'll be fine.

              

              
              
