          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Finally got my beer up and running. Two brews so far from kit, an American Pale and an English Brown. Both kits were designed for stovetop brewing with a 2.5 gallon wort with water added at end to make 5 gallons. I have the kit to brew full batch from begining though, so I started with 6 gallons on the APA (ended up with 4) and 7 gallons (closer to 5.5 at the end) for the Brown. Good initial fermentation action. Used a secondary for the APA because I needed the primary bucket for the second. Want to use second for the brown because I wasn't able to avoid the trub during transfer. Nailed the OG on the APA, forgot to measure on the Brown. Bottling in 10 days, will be brewing weekly for a while. 3.5 more kits and then it's all grain from there on out. One of my kits had a bad can of liquid extract so I'll mash up 6 lbs of grain as a transition batch. <br /><br />I'm excited to finally be doing this.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
