              Last year, because she is awesome, Mrs. Group gave me two hop rhizomes for our anniversary (Centennial and Cascade). I'm hoping to get usable hops from them this year, but it has dawned on me that I have no idea how to determine their alpha acid content. Now, generally speaking, I've got no problem brewing beer on a best-guess basis and having it be potentially fantastic but impossible to replicate.<br /><br />I do have a problem brewing beer that turns out undrinkable. So it seems like I'll want to know at least their approximate AAU numbers; I don't want to guesstimate 5 and have it be 8, for example.<br /><br />This has got to be a solved problem...right?

              

              
              
            </div>
