            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              OK, first batch is in the fermenter.  A few questions now though:<br /><br />1) The kit's estimated OG was 1.043, but my hydrometer reading came in closer to 1.039.  Is that likely to be a problem?  Any idea what I might have done wrong to cause that?<br /><br />2) The wort was really foamy after pouring it into the bucket, even before stirring it or adding the yeast.  I assume that normal, but the instructions didn't really mention it.<br /><br />3) The dry yeast pack says it will basically be done fermenting in 2-3 days.  However, the kit says to leave it in the fermenter for 1-2 weeks.  What's the best practice here?  Leave it in for the full 2 weeks?  Bottle after 1 week?<br /><br />A few of the upgrades people recommended over the basic kit really paid off.  My homemade wort chiller worked like a champ, especially after I started stirring.  212 to &lt;100 in about 10 minutes, and down to 75 in about 10 more minutes.  Also, the larger pot really paid off (I started with 3 gallons of liquid in a 5 gallon pot).  Didn't even come close to a boil over.  <br /><br />Next upgrade that I'm seeing a need for is a thief.  I used a sanitized turkey baster to fill the tube the hydrometer came in, but that didn't really work as smoothly as I would have liked.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
