              <div class="quotetitle">dak wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Quote:<br />1) The kit's estimated OG was 1.043, but my hydrometer reading came in closer to 1.039. Is that likely to be a problem? Any idea what I might have done wrong to cause that?<br /><br />Do you know how much water really boiled off?</div><br />Well, I started at 3 gallons of water (plus LME), and when I poured it into the bucket it ended up about halfway between the 2 gallon and 3 gallon marks.</div><br />OK, reading the fine print on my hydrometer, since I took the reading when the wort was about 75 degrees, I should have added about 0.002 to the reading, so it's actually 1.041 which isn't too far off of the estimated 1.043.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
