              <div class="quotetitle">DJ Immortal wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I was in Vermont today and stopped into a brewpub for lunch - my eye was immediately drawn to the brewing equipment and then to this painting.  Can anyone help ID the components?  <br /><br />MT = Mash Tun<br />HLB = Hot Liquor <strike>Bucket</strike>barrel(?)<br />CWP = ? (I figure that's where the boil takes place since it has brick insulation and a chimney <br />HP = Hops ____?<br />FV = Fermenting Vessel?<br />CT = Clarifying or Carbonating ___?<br /></div><br /><br />The B will be Back and the T Tank. CWP would be the Copper, but WP is drawing a blank. HP would conventionally be a Hop Back but it really does look like a P.<br /><br />Edit: There's no cooler shown after the Hop Back; perhaps it's Heat Pump.

              

              
              
