              After 2 days of pretty regular bubbling (once every 7 seconds like clockwork), my airlock now has zero activity.  I used Muntons dry yeast which I know can be pretty quick to ferment, and I used the whole packet even though I was doing a half batch, but that's much faster than I thought it would go.  Is there any harm in picking up the bucket and swirling it around a bit to mix things back up again?

              

              
              
