              <div class="quotetitle">dak wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">After 2 days of pretty regular bubbling (once every 7 seconds like clockwork), my airlock now has zero activity.  I used Muntons dry yeast which I know can be pretty quick to ferment, and I used the whole packet even though I was doing a half batch, but that's much faster than I thought it would go.  Is there any harm in picking up the bucket and swirling it around a bit to mix things back up again?</div><br /><br />no harm, but I'd leave it alone. I reguarly go 2 weeks in primary. you'll still have conversion going on, just not on a massive scale. your gravity will still be high with sugars.

              

              
              
