        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Well, I had planned on having my last Mr. Beer batch be ready to drink while I'm waiting for my first real batch to mature.  However, 4 weeks after bottling I tried one and it was... not good.  It had tasted a little off when I tried a sample while bottling, but I went ahead anyway figuring it would settle out eventually.  After my first not so good bottle, I let it sit for another couple of weeks and tried another bottle this weekend.  If anything, this one was worse.  <br /><br />Symptoms:<br />-fizzy, but zero head retention.  It's like soda.<br />-slight metallic taste, which is weird because the only metal it came in contact with was the can the extract came in and the stainless steel pot.<br />-an off flavor that I don't know how to identify based on the usual lists of off flavors.  Perhaps the &quot;solvent&quot; flavor?  Not sure really since I've never tasted solvent.  It doesn't really have an off smell, just a bad taste.<br />-horrible mouth feel.  It sort of burns my tongue and mouth.<br /><br />At this point, it's not even worth cooking with.  I'll let it sit for a while to see if it ever improves since I don't need the Mr. Beer bottles any more, but this was disappointment.  I'm wondering if I somehow got bacteria or wild yeast in there, or if maybe it fermented at too high of a temp, or maybe I just got a bad batch of extract.  5 weeks until my first specialty grain and extract batch is ready to drink.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
