              I had a batch that was neglected in secondary for about 3 months; I bottled it without pitching any yeast and it apparently did not have any living creatures left from the initial pitch. Let's just say that it's flat. <br />It, fortunately, tastes OK so will make a good cooking beer.<br /><br />We did bottle a farmhouse ale using a Belgian Saisan yeast 2 weeks ago; I cracked one of those last night and it is very nice. Low ABV, crisp, etc.

              

              
              
