              My American Pale Ale spent a week in primary and 2 in secondary and is ready to bottle. I just got my party pig delivered and am contemplating using it right away.<br /><br />Couple questions:  I'm not too concerned about labels and will soak for a few minutes in PBW solution, rinse by dipping in distilled water, and then into a bucket of starsan before bottling.  I've been judicious about rinsing these commercial microbrew bottles clear after drinking and I think this will be sufficient.<br /><br />-carboy cleaning. Will cleaning solution alone be enough to clean the better bottles?

              

              
              
